infringement offence
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a minor offence which carries an "instant fine" procedure, with the right to challenge the fine in court.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Jim Cameron writes : The concept originated in a special procedure (1957) for minor traffic offences. The scheme now applies eg to minor traffic, litter, liquor, and resource management offences.
